Stop Making Sense is a live 1984 album by Talking Heads, the soundtrack 
to the film of the same name. The original release of the album features 
only nine of the songs from the movie, many of them heavily edited. The 
album spent more than two years (118 weeks) on the Billboard 200 chart. 
In 1999, a 16-track re-release coincided with the concert's 15th 
anniversary.
